ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectAddition to Treaty Four Indian Reserve Grounds No. 77, Saskatchewan
PrecisOrder setting apart 0.8796 hectares (2.172 acres) of surface land, and 0.8286 hectares (2.046 acres) of mines and minerals, for the use and benefit of the Treaty Four First Nations as an addition to TREATY FOUR RESERVE GROUNDS NO. 77, located in the Town of Fort Qu'Appelle, Saskatchewan.
